# Solo IT Time Management Rule

## Session Start Protocol
- Start by checking latest files in `todo/` and `learner/`.
- Summarize: top 3 priorities, top 3 risks, blockers, and backlog delta.
- If no daily file exists for today, create:
  - `todo/YYYY-MM-DD.md`
  - `learner/YYYY-MM-DD.md`

## Task Definition Standard
- Every task must include: impact, estimate, deadline, owner (`you` or `agent`), and status.
- Use statuses only: `todo`, `in_progress`, `blocked`, `done`, `dropped`.
- If blocked for more than 1 day, add escalation action and owner.

## Daily Execution Discipline
- Plan using 3 focus blocks only (high-value tasks first).
- Keep work in progress <= 3 items.
- End of day must include: done list, not-done list, carry-forward, and tomorrow first task.

## Backlog and Timeline Control
- Keep one source of truth: `todo/backlog.md`.
- Every completed daily file must update backlog item status.
- Weekly review must identify overdue items and split oversized tasks.
- Every feature must map to a sprint/milestone and production readiness gate.

## Production Readiness Gate (Before Live)
- Required checks: tests pass, lint pass, rollback plan, monitoring, and risk notes.
- Track DORA baseline for each release: deployment frequency, lead time, change failure rate, MTTR.
- Track security baseline: secrets handling, dependency scan, vulnerability response owner/date.

## Non-Negotiable Don'ts
- Do not start coding before writing today priorities and constraints.
- Do not run unplanned tasks unless marked as urgent and logged in backlog delta.
- Do not close day without carry-forward and blocker status updates.
